	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I finally went to ToFS and got the bugger to spawn, so I've officially got every component I was told to retrieve. So I return to Kael, expecting something to go wrong since I've been reading / posting on this message board for the last few days, and as some others have discovered, Helssen hasn't been up since the patch. So I petitioned. Only a guide online, but I still got fed the same BS. Apparently the guide 'knew of no problems with the spawn of that NPC'. Deciding not to push it as one does when they're trying to get what they rightfully worked for, I just said 'ok, well thanks for your time :)'. The Guide told me that if the NPC doesn't respawn in a 'reasonable' amount of time, I should 'feel free to petition again'. And trust me, I will.<br><br>I've heard everything (from player sources) from 'they're nerfing the whole quest' to 'Helssen and the others were supposed to respawn as of this quest, but require Ally faction' so it's hard to tell what to believe. Looks like we're just going to have to wait and see. One thing I will say though. If this is their method of phasing it out, they need to rexamine their methods. If you want to stop the quest, you should stop it from the *begining*, not the end to prevent others from starting it (and ultimately wasting their time). And don't feed me any of that 'well maybe it wasn't technically possible BS.'<br>I'll return to the MB if anything changes.<br>Azara.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
